figgy.title: Order Manager doesn't display graphql error messages

comments.body:
We need to test [these lines of code](https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/i5370-graphql-error-alerts/app/javascript/store/vuex/actions.js#L88-L89). 

This type of test where we [test the commit and check the state for an update](https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/javascript/test/resource.spec.js#L83-L90), could potentially work.

We could also potentially [test the Vuex Action](https://vuex.vuejs.org/guide/testing.html#testing-actions) itself. Or we could do [a feature test on the Order Manager](https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/i5370-graphql-error-alerts/spec/features/order_manager_spec.rb).

Most of these require knowing how to break the test resource so that it throws an error when saving, which I'm not sure how to do.
